<br>
First issue:  Increased mitigation beyond 1300 AC is seemingly meaningless.  And with the availability of high AC all/all high end gear, it is completely feasible for all high end melee to reach 1300 AC, making a Warrior's supposed higher mitigation meaningless.<br>
<br>
Fixes:  Make mitigation beyond 1300 AC have impact.  Introduce Warrior only AC items which provide additional mitigation beyond what is possible for other melee classes.  Otherwise, develop a seperate defensive table for Warriors superior to other melee.<br>
<br>
Second issue:  A Warrior's inherently higher HP is becoming trivialized with the introduction of more high end HP gear.  <br>
<br>
Fixes:  Introduce Warrior only items which add significantly more HP than comparable items for other melee.  Otherwise, develop some form of a formula whereby Warriors get additional HP bonuses over and above what other melee classes would get with the same HP item.<br>
<br>
Third issue:  Taunt is broken, particularly when coupled with defensive.  Currently the work around for this is to get Warriors hard to find/aquire high agro weapons of which there are perhaps only a dozen in the game.<br>
<br>
Fixes:  Modify taunt so that it has greater functionality.  Forcing Warriors to rely solely on high agro weapons is unreasonable given how easily other classes can hold agro.  If modifying taunt isn't feasible, then make high agro weapons more available.<br>
<br>
Fourth issue:  Defensive has become a crutch and is a Warrior's three minutes of glory.  Either defensive is required and the Warrior drops after three minutes or its not required.  If its not required, a Warrior is not the best choice for tank.  Allowing someone to tank a boss mob for a total of three minutes is hard on the tank and hard on the raid.  People are learning to work around defensive.<br>
<br>
Fixes:  Introduce a seperate and superior defensive table for Warriors only as mentioned above.  This will make a Warrior the best choice for tank with or without defensive.  Also allowing AC above 1300 to have impact will improve this as well.  Defensive should be more of a last ditch save the raid ability rather than the basis of all high end raiding.  Other melee should not be a better choice for tank when not using defensive.          <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ulorddaeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lorddaeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/15/02 12:42:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=244>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> nice summary. mind if i steal it?<br>
